SIMPLE: overnight
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overnight
<hw>O"ver*night`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The fore part of
the night last past; the previous evening.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>overnight</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: overnight
<hw>o"ver*night"</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In the fore part
of the night last past; in the evening before.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Throughout the night; <as>as, the candle will not
last <ex>overnight</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>During the night; hence, in a short period of time;
<as>as, his prospects of winning changed
<ex>overnight</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>I had been telling her all that happened <qex>overnight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>overnight</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: overnight
<hw>o"ver*night"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Occurring or accomplished
during one night; <as>as, guaranteed <ex>overnight</ex> delivery of a
package</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overnoise</ent>⟦br⟧
